     <h1>About SEBI</h1>
     <div><img src="images/ora.jpg" width="1119" height="450" alt="content"/></div><br>
     <table width="100%" id="three">
            <tr>
                   <td colspan="2"> Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) is a statutory body set up by the Parliament in 1992 to protect the interests of investors and to regulate and develop the capital market.It started operations in 1988 through an order of Government of India.The key function of SEBI are focused upon development of indian securities market, regulation of various intermediaries in the securities market and protection of the interest of investors.It is head quartered in Mumbai width regional offices in Delhi, Kolkata, Chenni and Ahmedabad and various local offices across States.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                   <td width="50%">Buying and selling of shares take place in the stock exchanges through stock brokers. These intermediaries in securities market can function only if they are registered with SEBI.They are also required to follow the rules, regulations and guidelines laid down by SEBI to protect the investors. Similarly, SEBI also regulates other participants in the capital market like stock exchange, brokers,depositories,depository participants, protfolio managers,merchant bankers, share tranfer agents, etc.<br><br><b>For details of functions of SEBI, visit SEBI website at<br><br>( www.sebi.gov.in.)</b></td>
                   <td width="50%"><img src="images/w.jpg" width="700" height="300"> </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                   <td colspan="2">Mutual funds collect money from different investors and them invest that money in various schemes as per the choice of the investors. They are governed by rules formulated by SEBI. Mutual Funds have to diclose details of the schemes, where they will invest money, the fees charged from the investors etc. They also have to make periodic disclosures for the benefits of investors as mandated by SEBI.<br><br>SEBI also educates investors and facilitates Redressal of their Grienvance.
                   </td>
            </tr>
